The paper proposes a method for learning from demonstration using a variational neural model with auxiliary loss terms to ground abstract concepts such as spatial relations. This involves processing natural language instructions and high-dimensional sensory input streams. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
